The paper focuses on understanding and comparing RNN models for NLP tasks, which suggests that it belongs to the category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a visual analytics method for analyzing RNNs, which involves techniques related to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions using word clouds and glyph-based sequence visualization, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) for analyzing image data.
